  "text": "Yet another way of stabilizing the Galerkin method has been long pursued and defended by several authors. The idea was to stabilize by means of a proper choice of the grid. This includes the possibility of using a suitable refinement near the outflow boundary so that, actually, the stabilization is not needed anymore, like in the Shishkin meshes (see Ref. [CITATION_1] ",
